tiles.displayName: PeopleSoft Problem Logs by Entity Type
PeopleSoft Problem Logs by Label and Entity

dashboards.description: This dashboard provides an analytic view of logs from across the PeopleSoft application stack. It provides a focus on new issues seen today that were not seen in the prior day. Additional graphs provide histogram views of logs with problems, as well as logs across the application tiers, hosts, and database.

savedSearches.description: Histogram of logs from all PeopleSoft and Host sources based on Log Group

uiConfig.queryString: 'Log Group' = PSFT and 'Entity Type' in ('PSFT PIA', 'Host (Linux)', 'PSFT Process Scheduler Domain', 'PSFT Application Server Domain') | timestats count as logrecords by 'Log Source'

savedSearches.displayName: PeopleSoft Problem Logs by Entity Type
savedSearches.description: Problem log records by entity type based on Log Group

uiConfig.queryString: 'Log Group' in (PSFT) and 'Problem Priority' != null | fields Time | timestats count as logrecords by 'Entity Type'

savedSearches.description: Cluster comparison of last 24 hours to prior 24 hours over all logs related to the PeopleSoft infrastructure.

uiConfig.queryString: 'Log Group' = PSFT | fields Time, 'Log Group' | clustercompare timeshift = -24hour size = 24hour

savedSearches.description: Histogram of logs from all Database sources based on Log Group

uiConfig.queryString: 'Log Group' = PSFT and 'Entity Type' in ('Autonomous Transaction Processing', 'Oracle Database', 'Oracle Database Instance', 'Oracle Pluggable Database') | timestats count as logrecords by 'Log Source'

savedSearches.displayName: PeopleSoft Problem Logs by Label and Entity
savedSearches.description: Logs flagged as problem, grouped by label (problem) and entity based on Log Group

uiConfig.queryString: 'Log Group' in (PSFT) and 'Problem Priority' != null | fields Time | stats count as logrecords by Label, Entity
